{"explanation": "In this sentence, 'in which' introduces the relative clause '342 languages are currently active and 14 are closed' which modifies the preceding '344 languages of the world'. 'In which' here is equivalent to 'in the 344 languages of the world', indicating that among these languages, 342 are active and 14 are closed."}
```

```json
{"explanation": "In this sentence, the subject is '342 languages' and the predicate verb is 'are'. Since the subject is in plural form, the predicate verb also uses the plural form 'are', maintaining subject-verb agreement. Similarly, in '14 are closed', the subject '14' (referring to 14 languages) is also plural, so the predicate verb also uses the plural form 'are'."}
```

